{"id":72993,"title":"International outreach: what is the responsibility of ASTRO and the major international radiation oncology societies?","abstract":"In this era of globalization and rapid advances in radiation oncology worldwide, the American Society for Radiation Oncology (ASTRO) is committed to help decrease profound regional disparities through the work of the International Education Subcommittee (IES). The IES has expanded its base, reach, and activities to foster educational advances through a variety of educational methods with broad scope, in addition to committing to the advancement of radiation oncology care for cancer patients around the world, through close collaboration with our sister radiation oncology societies and other educational, governmental, and organizational groups.","date":"2014-06-15","categories":"Neoplasms","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24929158","annotations":[{"name":"Oncology","weight":0.692342,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oncology"},{"name":"Globalization","weight":0.642176,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Globalization"},{"name":"Radiation therapy","weight":0.637356,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiation_therapy"},{"name":"Radiation","weight":0.610865,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiation"},{"name":"Cancer","weight":0.585865,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer"},{"name":"United States","weight":0.471137,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States"},{"name":"Education","weight":0.27754,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Education"},{"name":"Society","weight":0.0227187,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Society"},{"name":"Major","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Major"},{"name":"Variety show","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Variety_show"},{"name":"Oscilloscope","weight":0.0168623,"wikip